  "text": "individual-level barriers-how individuals view and experience their encounters with the system (interpersonal and intrapersonal; [CITATION_1] ; see also [CITATION_2] . Among the barriers, stigma has been identified as the most significant (DHHS, 2001) because it is both a system-and individual-level barrier. Other system-level barriers include access issues (inaccessible location, transportation problems, and lack of health insurance), availability of services (few opportunities for group counseling and in-home services), social issues (lack of child care), poor quality of care (limited access to culturally competent clinicians and case management), and cultural matching (few opportunities to work with racial and ethnic minority clinicians; [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
